{
  "rules": {
    "rust-source-line-limits": {
      "description": "All Rust source files in the Yew frontend must remain strictly between 25 and 250 lines (inclusive).",
      "pattern": "frontend/src/**/*.rs",
      "check": {
        "type": "regex",
        "value": "^(?:.*\\n){25,250}$",
        "message": "Rust source files in the frontend must be between 25 and 250 lines."
      }
    }
  }
}

# Project Principles

- **Frontend Rust File Size Limit**: All Rust source files in the `frontend/src` directory must be strictly between 25 and 250 lines of code (inclusive). This ensures modularity, compile speed, and readability.
- **Code Modularity**: Extract string parsing, Operational Transformation helpers, and utility structures into dedicated modules (e.g. `collab_utils.rs`) rather than making core components too large.
- **Vanilla Styling**: All styling uses vanilla CSS variables inside `frontend/Assets/styles.css`. Avoid adding third-party styling frameworks.

# Project Structure

- **Backend (`src/`)**: Axum-based HTTP/WebSocket server. Manages collaborative note syncing, note persistence, and security settings.
- **Frontend (`frontend/`)**: Yew-based WebAssembly application compiled via Trunk.
  - `frontend/src/main.rs`: Application shell and route controller.
  - `frontend/src/collab.rs` & `frontend/src/collab_utils.rs`: Real-time operational transformation and cursor synchronizations.
  - `frontend/src/editor.rs` & `frontend/src/toolbar.rs`: Markdown editor layout, keybind shortcuts, and format toolbar.
  - `frontend/src/header.rs`: App header with notepad selector and multi-theme switcher.
  - `frontend/src/search.rs`: Fuzzy search query and preview snippet list.
  - `frontend/src/login.rs`: PIN security login view.